<h2>core/utils — Outdated Phase References</h2>
<p>These TODOs reference "Phase 6+" but all 10 phases are already complete. The commented-out code may need to be re-evaluated — either the integration was done differently elsewhere, or these are genuinely incomplete despite the phase being marked done.</p>

<table>
  <tr><th>File</th><th>Line</th><th>TODO</th><th>Status</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>pathInsertionMethods.ts</code></td>
    <td>45</td>
    <td>CustomTextNode upgrade — requires <code>CustomTextNodeRegistry</code> from injector chain. Currently returns <code>null</code> (no-op).</td>
    <td><strong>Investigate</strong> — Phase 8 (webexpressions) is complete. The <code>CustomTextNodeRegistry</code> exists. This stub may need wiring, or text node upgrades may be handled via a different path (e code>MutationObserver</code> in <code>InjectorRoot</code>).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>pathInsertionMethods.ts</code></td>
    <td>62</td>
    <td>CustomComment upgrade — requires <code>CustomComment</code>. Currently returns <code>null</code> (no-op).</td>
    <td><strong>Investigate</strong> — similar situation. Comment handling may be done elsewhere.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>pathInsertionMethods.ts</code></td>
    <td>101</td>
    <td>Attribute upgrade — requires <code>CustomAttribute</code>. Commented out.</td>
    <td><strong>Likely outdated</strong> — Phase 7 (webbehaviors) is complete. <code>CustomAttribute</code> exists and attribute handling is done via <code>CustomAttributeRegistry</code> + <code>MutationObserver</code>.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p>These stubs live in the DOM insertion path (<code>appendChild</code>, <code>insertBefore</code>, etc.). When a node is inserted into the DOM, <code>pathInsertionMethods</code> walks the subtree and upgrades undetermined elements. The question is whether text node, comment, and attribute upgrades also need to happen at insertion time, or whether they're already handled by the <code>MutationObserver</code> in <code>InjectorRoot</code>.</p>

